  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nI need to replace the validator for javax.validation.constraints.Email with a custom implementation.\r\nI found this example for programmaticly replacing the validator behind a constraint: https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/validator/6.2/reference/en-US/html_single/#section-programmatic-constraint-definition\r\nThis custom validator should apply for the default validator factory, which lead me to believe I need to use something like this: https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/validator/6.2/reference/en-US/html_single/#section-programmatic-api-contributor\r\n\r\nThere is however no way right now to retrieve the ConstraintMappingContributor for the default validator factory in quarkus.\r\n\r\n(This follow up https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/How.20to.20wire.20up.20an.20ConstraintMappingContribu)\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nThe jackson ObjectMapper in quarkus is configured by calling all implementations of `ObjectMapperCustomizer#customize` (see\r\nhttps://quarkus.io/guides/rest-json#json).\r\n\r\nSomething similar could be done for HV. I.e. call all implementations of `ConstraintMappingContributor#createConstraintMappings`.",
